18/12/2002
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH Standing Committee for Military Matters (SCMM) chief will attend central government sessions starting next year, according to NATO Operations and Crisis Management Department chief Robert Serry.
Speaking on Tuesday (17 December), he added that the notion was proposed by NATO Secretary General George Robertson in a letter to BiH authorities earlier this year.
The SCMM chairman will attend the sessions, but not vote.
(OHR Sources - 18/12/02;
PBS BiH - 17/12/02)
